SIMPLE: experimentalist
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Experimentalist
<hw>Ex*per`i*men"tal*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
makes experiments, especially one who likes to experiment; an
experimenter.</def> <rj><au>Whaterly.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who relies primarily on experimentation and the
evidence of one's own senses; an empiricist; -- contrasted with
<contr>theoretician</contr> or <contr>dogmatist</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Experimentalize</ent>⟦br⟧
